## Conflicts Identified and Resolved

### Testing Status Conflict
- **CURRENT_STATE_BASELINE.md**: Claims 91.7% test pass rate
- **CLAUDE.md**: Reports 117 test failures, critical infrastructure issues
- **RESOLUTION**: CLAUDE.md is more recent (August 2025) and critical status takes precedence

### Development Priority Conflict
- **TODO.md**: Focuses on enhancement features (quiz improvements, visualizations)
- **CLAUDE.md**: States testing infrastructure repair required before feature development
- **RESOLUTION**: Testing repair must be Priority 1 before any feature development

### Northwestern Implementation Status
- **Phase_4_Foundation_Assessment.md**: Treats as future possibility
- **System_Status_Update_2025_01_18.md**: Definitively states 0% complete, separate initiative
- **RESOLUTION**: Northwestern is deferred initiative, not active development

## Content Consolidation Strategy

### Current System Status Section
- Merged accurate technical details from README.md and CURRENT_STATE_BASELINE.md
- Integrated critical testing status from CLAUDE.md
- Included honest assessment from System_Status_Update

### Active Development Tasks Section
- Prioritized testing infrastructure repair from CLAUDE.md (CRITICAL)
- Included Phase 4 preparation from Phase_4_Foundation_Assessment.md
- Incorporated realistic tasks from TODO.md (post-testing-repair)

### Future Enhancement Roadmap Section
- Extracted Phase 4 pathways from Phase_4_Foundation_Assessment.md
- Included backlog features from TODO.md
- Maintained realistic timelines and effort estimates

### Deferred Initiatives Section
- Northwestern implementation from System_Status_Update (5-6 month separate initiative)
- Advanced features requiring stable foundation
- Research and experimental capabilities

## Redundancy Elimination

### Duplicate Technical Architecture Information
- Consolidated React architecture details (single source from README.md)
- Merged performance metrics from multiple sources
- Unified component structure descriptions

### Overlapping Development Planning
- Eliminated duplicate task descriptions across TODO.md and assessments
- Consolidated timeline information into single progression
- Merged priority systems into unified P1-P4 structure

### Strategic Assessment Repetition
- Single foundation readiness assessment (from Phase_4_Foundation_Assessment.md)
- Consolidated medical education value statements
- Unified stakeholder communication messages

## Medical Education Focus Maintained
- All content prioritizes medical education value and clinical workflow integration
- Evidence-based development approaches preserved
- Professional medical accuracy standards maintained throughout
- Clinical emergency access requirements (<30 seconds) integrated

## Success Metrics
- **6 source files** successfully analyzed and consolidated
- **3 major conflicts** identified and resolved
- **4 content areas** organized with clear hierarchy
- **Single source of truth** created for all planning needs
- **Medical accuracy** maintained throughout consolidation
- **Realistic assessment** preserved from all accurate sources